%I A396368 #73 May 31 2026 17:41:33
%S A396368 242,55,212,232,4,444,555,96769,1153511,137636731
%N A396368 Smallest center of a 3 X 3 magic square whose entries are nonnegative palindromes and exactly n of them are palindromic primes.
%C A396368 Each term in a given magic square is required to have the same number of decimal digits.
%C A396368 See Examples and Rebert and Rosa links for the magic squares themselves.
%H A396368 Jean-Marc Rebert, <a href="/A396368/a396368_3.txt">Palindromic magic squares</a>
%H A396368 Carlos Rivera, <a href="https://www.primepuzzles.net/problems/prob_093.htm">Problem 93. A couple of SG 3x3 magic squares composed only by distinct palprimes</a>
%H A396368 Carlos Rivera and Jaime Ayala, World!Of Numbers, <a href="https://www.worldofnumbers.com/palprim3.htm#crivera">Magic Squares composed of only palprimes</a>
%H A396368 Jean Claude Rosa, World!Of Numbers, <a href="https://www.worldofnumbers.com/won129.htm">Magic Squares composed of only Palindromic Primes</a>
%e A396368 a(4) = 4, since all entries of the following 3 X 3 magic square are palindromes, and exactly 4 of them are prime:
%e A396368   3* 2* 7*
%e A396368   8  4  0
%e A396368   1  6  5*
%e A396368 a(5) = 444, since all entries of the following 3 X 3 magic square are palindromes, and exactly 5 of them (*) are prime:
%e A396368   414  161  757*
%e A396368   787* 444  101*
%e A396368   131* 727* 474
%e A396368 Moreover, no 3 X 3 magic squares with this property exist with smaller central values.
%e A396368 From _Michael S. Branicky_, May 24 2026: (Start)
%e A396368 a(3) = 232, arising from the magic square
%e A396368   141  313* 242
%e A396368   333  232  131
%e A396368   222  151* 323 (End)
%Y A396368 Cf. A000040, A002113, A002385, A145314, A260254, A341156.
%K A396368 nonn,base,fini,full
%O A396368 0,1
%A A396368 _Jean-Marc Rebert_, May 24 2026
%E A396368 a(3) corrected by and a(9) due to Jean Claude Rosa from _Michael S. Branicky_, May 24 2026
